snippet.textDisplay: My mom suffers from narcolepsy and sleep apnea that has gotten worse as she's aged. She gets extremely embarassed when we rent movies or are spending time together at home and she spontaneously and uncontrollably passes out. We can't afford the surgeries and medicine needed to treat it, so I try to at least lessen her negative feelings towards what she can't control by giving her full mani-pedis while she's passed out. It's kinda like adding a little bit of sparkle to a sad situation. She really loves having her nails done and gets a confidence boost when people compliment her on them at work. It's alot of fun and really is kind of like a nice surprise to do someone's nails in their sleep.
